Epigynum (
Figs 89–90
): wider than long, with a large transverse central depression; copulatory openings in anterio-lateral sides of depression; internally, copulatory tubes proceed anteriorly, then loop around before turning posteriorly to end anterolaterally in small round spermathecae; fertilization ducts exit spermathecae posteromedially.
